default&#xa0;defaultAs way of background, The British Association for Counselling and Psychotherapy (BACP) is the leading and largest professional body for counselling and psychotherapy in Europe, 
defaultwith a membership of 
defaultover 38
default,000 practitioners
default, 
defaultdrawn from the various professional disciplines in the field of counselling and psychotherapy and based in a range of settings.
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultAll BACP members are bound by the Ethical Framework for Good Practice for Counselling and Psychotherapy and within this, the Professional Conduct Procedure.
